      "area": "Courier selection algorithm",
      "evolution_path": "Currently simple nearest-available. Can evolve to scoring models (rating, delivery history, vehicle type) by changing the ORDER BY clause and adding a lightweight scoring function. No architectural change needed."
    },
    {
      "area": "Event consumption mechanism",
      "evolution_path": "Start with HTTP webhooks from Order service. Can migrate to Kafka/SQS when volume demands it. The Order Events Consumer adapter isolates this change."
    },
    {
      "area": "Geographic query strategy",
      "evolution_path": "Start with zone-based filtering (simple string match). Can evolve to PostGIS spatial queries for precise radius-based matching without changing the architecture — just the query."
    }
  ],

  "rigidity_points": [
    {
      "area": "Single-primary write path",
      "reason": "All assignment writes go through one PostgreSQL primary. This is intentionally rigid — it's the mechanism that guarantees no double-assignment. Horizontal write scaling would require sharding by geography, which is a major architectural change. Acceptable up to ~1,000 assignments/second on modern hardware."
