      "DO NOT use an ORM for the assignment transaction — hand-written SQL is critical for correctness and performance here",
      "DO NOT add Redis 'for caching' — it doubles your infrastructure and failure modes for marginal benefit at this scale",
      "DO NOT implement distributed sagas or event sourcing — the entire assignment is one atomic transaction, keep it that way",
      "DO NOT use async replication hoping it's 'good enough' — a lost assignment after failover means a double-assignment",
      "DO NOT skip the stuck-assignment reaper — without it, courier capacity silently leaks over time"
    ]
  },

