    {
      "type": "missing_constraints",
      "description": "Unknown scale parameters: How many concurrent orders per second? How many couriers in the system? What geographic distribution? The single-primary PostgreSQL approach handles ~1,000 assignments/second comfortably. If the platform expects 10,000+/second, we'd need geographic sharding (each region gets its own DB), which is a fundamentally different architecture.",
      "options": [
