        "B: Geographically sharded PostgreSQL — each city/region has its own primary, good to ~50,000/sec, but adds routing complexity and cross-region assignment is impossible",
        "C: CockroachDB or Spanner — distributed SQL with strong consistency, scales horizontally, but much higher operational complexity and cost"
      ],
